   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <hazardstatement type="danger" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">hazard of electric shock,
                  explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">
                  <sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Electrical equipment must be installed, operated,
                        serviced, and maintained only by qualified personnel.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Apply appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE)
                        and follow safe electrical work practices.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Disconnection devices for AC and DC must be provided
                        by others, be readily accessible, and the function of the disconnect device
                        marked for its function.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Turn off all power supplying the UPS system before
                        working on or inside the equipment.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Before working on the UPS system, check for hazardous
                        voltage between all terminals including the protective earth.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">The UPS contains an internal energy source. Hazardous
                        voltage can be present even when disconnected from the mains supply. Before
                        installing or servicing the UPS system, ensure that the units are OFF and
                        that mains and batteries are disconnected. Wait five minutes before opening
                        the UPS to allow the capacitors to discharge.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">The UPS must be properly earthed/grounded and due to
                        a high leakage current, the earthing/grounding conductor must be connected
                        first.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note class="- topic/note ">This procedure shows the 80 kVA UPS but the procedure is
            identical for all UPS systems.</note>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Loosen the six screws and remove the indicated
               plate.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image
                     href="../Images/img_80_kva_replace_the_interface_board_remove_plate_in_front_of_board_0000102051.png"
                     scalefit="yes" scope="local" placement="inline" class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Note the location of the cables connected to 0P2562
               and disconnect the cables.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Slide out the 0P2562 board to be replaced.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image
                     href="../Images/img_80_kva_replace_power_0j-0p2562_slide_out_0j-0p2562_0000102159.png"
                     scalefit="yes" scope="local" placement="inline" class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reverse the procedure for installation of the
               replacement 0P2562 board.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
